content:
The natural wonder you are referring to is the Grand Canyon, located in Arizona, USA. It is one of the most stunning and iconic geological formations in the world.

Here are some geological facts about the Grand Canyon in LaTeX format that you can include in your postcard:

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\begin{document}

\section*{Geological Facts about the Grand Canyon}

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Age:} The rock layers of the Grand Canyon span nearly 2 billion years of Earth's history.
    \item \textbf{Formation:} The canyon itself was carved by the Colorado River over the last 5-6 million years.
    \item \textbf{Geology:} The canyon exposes \textit{Paleozoic}, \textit{Mesozoic}, and \textit{Proterozoic} rocks.
    \item \textbf{Depth:} The average depth of the canyon is about 1,600 meters (5,250 feet), with the deepest point being over 1,800 meters (about 6,000 feet).
    \item \textbf{Width:} At its widest point, the canyon stretches approximately 29 kilometers (18 miles) across.
    \item \textbf{Length:} The Grand Canyon is approximately 446 kilometers (277 miles) long.
    \item \textbf{Erosion:} The principal force shaping the canyon is erosion, primarily by water, ice, and wind.
    \item \textbf{Stratigraphy:} Some of the most notable rock formations include the \textit{Kaibab Limestone}, \textit{Coconino Sandstone}, and \textit{Vishnu Schist}.
\end{itemize}

\end{document}
```

You can customize this LaTeX snippet to fit your preferences or add more details. Your friend will surely appreciate the mix of geological detail and the elegance of LaTeX formatting!
